The pistol featured a rotary locking barrel, straight-line trigger pull, and passive internal safety. This example, no. 2,351 of 3,000, retains virtually all of its original blue finish while the Palo Alto grip panels with inset Colt medallions are similarly in practically new condition. The pistol is housed in its original blue plastic case with cardboard carton and comes with: two 15 rd. magazines, loading tool, cleaning brush, warranty card, manual, and American Rifleman article excerpt from 1992 detailing the pistol. Also included is a 1991 dated Colt factory letter that lists a shipping date of October 24, 1991, to Midwest Recreational Shooting Supply of Ashland, OH. These pistols were intended to function much like a double-action revolver in the hopes of garnering police sales during the general transition over to semi-autos in the late '80s and early '90s, but never proved popular. They are seldom seen today and this example is in practically new condition; a rare late 20th century Colt. 
Ready to ship to your local dealer

title: For Sale/Trade:  Zastava PAP M92 AK Pistol **SALE PENDING**
postcontent:
I have a Zastava PAP M92 AK Pistol up for grabs. It is chambered in 7.62x39mm. I would rather sell, but will consider certain trade offers. Pistol comes with the following:

1) Hogue Grip
2) Echo 93 Sling Mount
3) Single-point Sling (not pictured)
4) Midwest Industries Handguard
5) Midwest Industries Flash Hider
6) Indent Pin and Spring installed to hold flash hider (not a pin and weld job)
7) Rail Covers (currently an OD green and black combo)
8) Angled Foregrip
9) Flashlight and Red Laser ($40 CP wallyworld brand, but it works and has held up)
10) Original Wood Handguard which has been refinished (stained and polyurethane) (not pictured)
11) Two metal mags

Pistol has been shot on two occasions, seen 5-6 boxes of non-corrosive Tula Ammo through it (so 100 - 120 rds), and has been meticulously cleaned and cared for. Yes, I baby my firearms. I bought it because I'm a big AK fan and thought I would like this and it turns out I don't. Ran with zero malfunctions of any kind, but in my humble opinion it just isn't a practical firearm. I prefer something with a stock. Make no mistake though, it is FUN to shoot and it really barks when it fires! Definitely a head turner at the range (not that thats a great reason to purchase a firearm but it doesn't hurt either). Will be using the money for another AK purchase.

Yes, you can get a plain Jane one of these with a wood handguard for less at fleet farm and if that's what you're looking for, great! If you want one where you don't have to piece together the bells and whistles and for less than what you would pay in product and shipping, then this one is for you.

Conditions of the sale/trade:
1) Buyer/trader MUST have a CURRENT AND VALID MN ID. NO EXCEPTIONS.
2) Buyer/trader MUST have a CURRENT MN PTP OR PTC and be willing to present it at the time of sale/trade. NO EXCEPTIONS.
3) Buyer/trader MUST be at least 21 years of age. NO EXCEPTIONS.
4) Both myself and the buyer/trader will complete a Bill of Sale and both of us will receive a signed copy. NO EXCEPTIONS.
5) I am not willing to ship, so FTF transactions only. I prefer to do business around the St. Peter/Mankato area.

Any questions, just shoot me an email. Am happy to send additional pics upon request. I do work for a living so please forgive me if I don't respond to emails during the 8am - 5pm hours of the workweek. Rest assured, I will return your message as soon as possible.  Thanks for looking.
